@I_amDorris your go to hack to never run out of content ideas

If you're a business owner on YouTube, you will never run out of content ideas. 

Sounds contradictory, but the reason is really simple. 

Every objection you hear on a sales call is a video waiting to be made. 

Think about it like this. 

If you're on a sales call and someone asks:

"Why should I hire an agency instead of doing it myself?"

That's not just one person's concern. 

Hundreds of your future prospects are already thinking the same exact way. 

They will ask you this on a sales call themselves. 

So turn it into a video. 

Film it once. Answer it thoroughly. Give context, examples, proof, basically everything you'd say on a sales call...

But better 

Because you had time to structure it properly. 

After you do this, two things happen simultaneously. 

>First, you never stare at a blank idea sheet again. Your sales calls are writing your videos for you. Every objection you get is a video topic. 

>Second, you build a library of objection-handling assets. Next time a prospect raises the same concern, or even before a sales call altogether, you can send them the video. 

Now they get a 10-minute deep dive instead of a 3-sentence reply or a 30-second answer on a call. 

They see your face, the way you think, and most importantly, the proof you introduced to back it up. 

By the time they show up on a call, the objection is already handled. 

Meanwhile, your competitors are answering the same exact thing over and over on every single call.
